<TITLE> Cyclone, heat waves forecast for April </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 4 (bdnews24.com)A cyclone along with mild to moderate heat waves are likely to sweep the country in April, with the possibility too of flash floods, the met office said on Saturday. Met office chief Sujit Kumar Dev Sharma told bdnews24.com that precipitation has been scarce for this time of year due to absence of a western wind, but rainfall would pick up soon. It predicted that a strong nor'-westerly was likely to blow over the country. April's weather forecast also warned of two depressions likely to occur in the Bay of Bengal one of which may develop into a cyclone. The weathermen say two to three moderate heat waves of 38-40 degrees Celcius are likely to prevail over the northern and middle regions, and three to four mild heat waves in other parts of the country. Sharma said temperatures would abate with rainfalls. The month is likely to see normal precipitation after the recent dry spell. River flow will remain normal, but there would be danger of flash floods in the northeast towards the end of the month, said the weather office. bd
